Install lighttpd:
apt-get install lighttpd

In '/etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf' modify the filed 'server.document-root' 
to 'www' folder in bloatit.
Example:
server.document-root       = "/home/fred/projets/bloatit/www"

Uncomment 'mod_rewrite' in 'server.modules'

In '/etc/lighttpd/conf-available/10-fastcgi.conf', replace 'fastcgi.server'
settings by the python one. Example:

fastcgi.server = (
    "serve.py" =>
    (
        "python-fcgi" =>
        (
         "socket" => "/tmp/fastcgi.python.socket",
         "bin-path" => "/usr/bin/python /home/fred/projets/bloatit/src/bloatit/fcgiserver/serve.py",
         "check-local" => "disable",
         "min-procs" => 1,
         "max-procs" => 1,
        )
    ))

Create a symbolic link of '10-fastcgi.conf' in '/etc/lighttpd/conf-enabled/':
cd /etc/lighttpd/conf-enabled/
ln -s ../conf-available/10-fastcgi.conf

Create a symbolic link of 'rewrite.lighttpd.conf' in '/etc/lighttpd/conf-enabled/':
cd /etc/lighttpd/conf-enabled/
ln -s /home/fred/projets/bloatit/lighttpd/rewrite.lighttpd.conf

Reload lighttpd config:
service lighttpd reload

Verify the loading in logs:
cat /var/log/lighttpd/error.log

Test it: http://127.0.0.1/serve.py

